Terraform Count Meta Argument and Count Index with example | count vs for_each demo tutorial

#Terraform Count Meta Argument is one of the resource meta arguments that lets you create multiple resources easily.

For more information on COUNT Meta Argument, Check out Terraform Official Documentation:
https://developer.hashicorp.com/terraform/language/meta-arguments/count




Here we are going Create more than 1 instances as many as we want including its name as well.

• count.index — The distinct index number (starting with 0 ) corresponding to this instance.
